ciscoDSGTuning.name: ciscoDSGTuning

revisions.description: V01.00.10 2012-11-19 Updated to support MOIP Input.
V01.00.09 2010-10-13 Updated for migrating D985X/D9865 MIB to generic logic.
V01.00.08 2010-08-03 New items inputStatusAsiLock, inputStatusAsiLinkError and inputStatusAsiPacketSize added in Input Status Table.
V01.00.07 2010-06-17 The enum options of satSignalFecRate, satSignalPolar and siInfoRxType and the description of satSignalAFC are updated.
V01.00.06 2010-05-03 Packet Error Count item name updated.
V01.00.05 2010-04-12 New MIB objects are added.
V01.00.04 2010-03-22 The Syntax of Unsigned32 MIB objects whose range is within the range of Integer32, is updated to Integer32.
V01.00.03 2010-02-12 The Syntax of read-only objects is updated to DisplayString.
V01.00.02 2010-01-18 Changed the enumerated value of object siRcvOptionStatusFreqSel from preset(2) to userCfg(2).
V01.00.01 2009-12-20 Added new object, activeTuningValidateOrbPos under activeTuning Group.

activeTuningValidateOrbPos.name: activeTuningValidateOrbPos
activeTuningValidateOrbPos.description: Command used to validate orbital position. Set this object to yes( 2 ) to validate Orbital position.

activeTuningChScan.name: activeTuningChScan
activeTuningChScan.description: Channel Scan command. Setting scan( 1 ) triggers the channel scanning process.

activeTunerFreq.name: activeTunerFreq
activeTunerFreq.description: The Satellite Downlink frequency in the range of 0 to 15000000 KHz in steps of 1 KHz.

activeTunerSymbolRate.name: activeTunerSymbolRate
activeTunerSymbolRate.description: Data rate on the transport stream in millions of symbols per second. Range is from 10000 to 450000 hectoSym/second in steps of 1 hectoSym/second. ( 1 hecto = 10^2 ).

activeTunerDVBSFEC.name: activeTunerDVBSFEC
activeTunerDVBSFEC.description: Forward Error Correction Rate. For DVB-S2 modulation only auto is applicable. For DVB-S modulation all options are applicable.

activeTunerRollOff.name: activeTunerRollOff
activeTunerRollOff.description: Alpha filtering - for DVB-S: 0.20/0.35, for DVB-S2: 0.20/0.25/0.35. Roll off with scaling factor of 1/100.

activeInputLNBType.name: activeInputLNBType
activeInputLNBType.description: LNB Type: C-Band/Single Ku/Dual Ku/Advanced. For simplified setup select C-Band or Ku-Band. If there is a need to configure LO, select Advanced.

activeInputLNBTrim.name: activeInputLNBTrim
activeInputLNBTrim.description: Low Noise Block Trim Level 1 when type is not advanced. It has a range of 0 to 15000000 KHz in steps of 1KHz.

activeInputLNBTrim2.name: activeInputLNBTrim2
activeInputLNBTrim2.description: Low Noise Block Trim Level 2 when type is not advanced. It has a range of 0 to 15000000 KHz in steps of 1KHz.

activeInputLocalOscFreq1.name: activeInputLocalOscFreq1
activeInputLocalOscFreq1.description: RW, only when LNB Type is Advanced. Local Oscillator #1 Frequency when type is advanced. It has a range of 0 to 15000000 KHz in steps of 1KHz.

activeInputLocalOscFreq2.name: activeInputLocalOscFreq2
activeInputLocalOscFreq2.description: RW, only when LNB Type is Advanced. Local Oscillator #2 Frequency when type is advanced. It has a range of 0 to 15000000 KHz in steps of 1KHz.

activeInputCrossOver.name: activeInputCrossOver
activeInputCrossOver.description: Crossover Frequency for Local Oscillator. It has a range of 0 to 15000000 KHz in steps of 1KHz.

activeInputOrbitalPos.name: activeInputOrbitalPos
activeInputOrbitalPos.description: Orbital location Azimuth.The range is from 0 to 3600 in steps of 1. The scaling factor is 1/10th of a degree.

activeInputSatName.name: activeInputSatName
activeInputSatName.description: Satellite Name Matching the Orbital Position + E/W Flag. Enter Satellite/Transponder Name to fill in Azimuth and E/W Flag automatically.

lnbPowerControl.name: lnbPowerControl
lnbPowerControl.description: Active LNB Power setting.13/18V is to control dual polarity LNB. The convention is: Horizontal-18V; Vertical-13V. Valid settings are, Off 13V ( 13V always, ignore polarity in NIT ) 18V ( 18V always, ignore polarity in NIT ) 13V-NIT ( 13V initially, over-ride by polarity in NIT ) 18V-NIT ( 18V initially, over-ride by polarity in NIT ).

lnbPowerStatus.name: lnbPowerStatus
lnbPowerStatus.description: Low Noise Block Power Supply Status.

satSignalPvBer.name: satSignalPvBer
satSignalPvBer.description: Status: DVB-S Post-Viterbi Bit Error Rate.

satSignalQPSKBer.name: satSignalQPSKBer
satSignalQPSKBer.description: Status: Quadrature phase-shift keying ( QPSK ) Bit error rate.

satSignalLdpCber.name: satSignalLdpCber
satSignalLdpCber.description: Status: DVB-S2 Low Density Parity Check Bit Error Rate.

satSignalCnMargin.name: satSignalCnMargin
satSignalCnMargin.description: Status: Carrier to Noise Ratio Link Margin.

satSignalSatDishCnMargin.name: satSignalSatDishCnMargin
satSignalSatDishCnMargin.description: Status: SatDish CN Margin in dB Displays the margin in dB to a threshold level at which failure occurs. The range is 0dB to 10dB.

satSignalSatDishSigLevel.name: satSignalSatDishSigLevel
satSignalSatDishSigLevel.description: Status: SatDish Signal level( in dBm ) plus some kind of graphical signal level meter on the LCD (the range is -75 dBm to +-20 dBm).

satSignalAfc.name: satSignalAfc
satSignalAfc.description: Status: Tuner Frequency Offset. The range is from -51.0 to 51.0 in steps of 0.1 MHz.

satSignalUncorErrCnt.name: satSignalUncorErrCnt
satSignalUncorErrCnt.description: Status: Uncorrected Error Counter. The range is from 0 to 4294967295.

satSignalCorErrCnt.name: satSignalCorErrCnt
satSignalCorErrCnt.description: Status: DVB-S Reed-Solomon Corrected Error Counter.

satSignalDnLkFreq.name: satSignalDnLkFreq
satSignalDnLkFreq.description: Status: Downlink Frequency in the range of 0.000000 to 15.000000 GHz in steps of 0.000001 GHz.

satSignalLbandFreq.name: satSignalLbandFreq
satSignalLbandFreq.description: Status: L-Band Frequency in the range of 950.000 to 2150.000 MHz in steps of 0.001 MHz.

satSignalSymbolRate.name: satSignalSymbolRate
satSignalSymbolRate.description: Status: Symbol Rate in the Range of 1.0000 to 45.0000 MegaSym/second in steps of 0.0001 MegaSym/second.

satSignalLnbPsStatus.name: satSignalLnbPsStatus
satSignalLnbPsStatus.description: Status: Low Noise Block Power Supply Status.

satSignalClearSigErrCnt.name: satSignalClearSigErrCnt
satSignalClearSigErrCnt.description: Set this variable to yes( 2 ) to clear signal error counter.

satSignalValidateOrbPosDate.name: satSignalValidateOrbPosDate
satSignalValidateOrbPosDate.description: Status: Last Orbital Position Validate Date.

satSignalFecSyncStatus.name: satSignalFecSyncStatus
satSignalFecSyncStatus.description: FEC SYNC Status for DVB-S PV Decoder.

inputStatusCurInput.name: inputStatusCurInput
inputStatusCurInput.description: Status: Current Input for D9865 only.

inputStatusInputRate.name: inputStatusInputRate
inputStatusInputRate.description: Status: Input Rate in Mega bauds per second ( Mbps ). The range is from 0.000000 to 4294.967295 Mbps in steps of 0.000001 Mbps.

inputStatusLastTuneReason.name: inputStatusLastTuneReason
inputStatusLastTuneReason.description: Status: Reason for the last tune.

inputStatusCurD985xInput.name: inputStatusCurD985xInput
inputStatusCurD985xInput.description: Status: Current Input for all IRD models.

inputStatusIpiSignal.name: inputStatusIpiSignal
inputStatusIpiSignal.description: Status: IPI Signal Encapsulation Lock Status.

inputStatusIpiPcrLock.name: inputStatusIpiPcrLock
inputStatusIpiPcrLock.description: Status: Indicates if PCR is received without errors or not.

siRcvOptionReacq.name: siRcvOptionReacq
siRcvOptionReacq.description: Set this variable to yes( 2 ) to reacquire signal.

siRcvOptionInputSel.name: siRcvOptionInputSel
siRcvOptionInputSel.description: UserCfg locks to RF input set by the user and SW Map uses Orbital Position settings to select RF input. It is recommended to set Validate Orbital Position to 'Yes' for SW Mapped option.

siRcvOptionFreqSel.name: siRcvOptionFreqSel
siRcvOptionFreqSel.description: Custom Tuning Mode: Frequency Tuning Mode: NIT/Preset.

siRcvOptionServListMode.name: siRcvOptionServListMode
siRcvOptionServListMode.description: Custom Tuning Mode: Service List Mode: Rigorous/Degraded.

siRcvOptionUseBAT.name: siRcvOptionUseBAT
siRcvOptionUseBAT.description: Custom Tuning Mode:Bouquet Association Table in Service List.

siRcvOptionUseNIT.name: siRcvOptionUseNIT
siRcvOptionUseNIT.description: Custom Tuning Mode:Network Information Table in Service List.

siRcvOptionUseSDT.name: siRcvOptionUseSDT

siRcvOptionLastActivated.name: siRcvOptionLastActivated
siRcvOptionLastActivated.description: Last Preset Activated number.The range is from 0 to 64.

siRcvOptionStatusUseBAT.name: siRcvOptionStatusUseBAT
siRcvOptionStatusUseBAT.description: Status of Bouquet Association Table in Service List.

siRcvOptionStatusUseNIT.name: siRcvOptionStatusUseNIT

siInfoRxInstance.name: siInfoRxInstance
siInfoRxInstance.description: Instance of SI Info Receive table.

siInfoRxIDExt.name: siInfoRxIDExt
siInfoRxIDExt.description: Service Information Receive Table ID Extension. The range is from 0 to 4294967295.

siInfoRxUid.name: siInfoRxUid
siInfoRxUid.description: Service Information Receive Unique ID. The range is from 1 to 32.

siInfoRxVer.name: siInfoRxVer

siInfoTsFreq.name: siInfoTsFreq
siInfoTsFreq.description: Frequency Plan: Service Information Frequency The range is from 0.000000 to 15.000000 GHz in steps of 0.000001 GHz.

siInfoTsSymRate.name: siInfoTsSymRate
siInfoTsSymRate.description: Frequency Plan: Service Information Symbol Rate. The range is from 1.0000 to 45.0000 Megasym/second in steps of 0.0001 Megasym.

siInfoTsOrbPosn.name: siInfoTsOrbPosn
siInfoTsOrbPosn.description: Frequency Plan: Service Information Orbital Position. The range is from 0.0 to 360.0 .

siInfoTsFEC.name: siInfoTsFEC

siInfoTsOrgNetID.name: siInfoTsOrgNetID
siInfoTsOrgNetID.description: Frequency Plan: Service Information Original Network ID. The range is from 0 to 4294967295.

siInfoTsEastWestFlag.name: siInfoTsEastWestFlag
siInfoTsEastWestFlag.description: Frequency Plan: Service Information East West flag.

siInfoVCInfoId.name: siInfoVCInfoId
siInfoVCInfoId.description: Service Information VC Service ID. The range is from 0 to 4294967295.

siInfoVCInfoTxID.name: siInfoVCInfoTxID
siInfoVCInfoTxID.description: Service Information VC Transport Stream ID. The range is from 0 to 4294967295.

siInfoVCInfoPMTPID.name: siInfoVCInfoPMTPID
